</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9983A9D91B1CFFD0FF00F790FCCCF3F7" pageId="2" pageNumber="513" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="D126FA521B1CFFD0FF00F790FCCCF3F7" blockId="2.[145,1354,2613,3234]" pageId="2" pageNumber="513">
<emphasis id="E3ED26401B1CFFD0FF00F790FCDBF3DE" bold="true" box="[148,843,3041,3074]" pageId="2" pageNumber="513">Movements, Home range and Social organization.</emphasis>
There is no specific information for this species, but the Bicolored Tuco-tuco is solitary.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9983A9D91B1CFFD0FF01F041FEC8F3A6" pageId="2" pageNumber="513" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="D126FA521B1CFFD0FF01F041FEC8F3A6" blockId="2.[145,1354,2613,3234]" pageId="2" pageNumber="513">
<emphasis id="E3ED26401B1CFFD0FF01F041FE67F38D" bold="true" box="[149,503,3120,3153]" pageId="2" pageNumber="513">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
The Bicolored Tuco-tuco has not yet been assessed on The IUCN Red List.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
